The course has both a chronological and a thematic focus. Key events of the 20th century British and Irish histories are studied decade by decade while some prevalent topics (the emancipation of women, the Irish question, the demise of the British Empire, the development of democracy and of popular culture, immigration issues) are dealt with thematically. Lectures are complemented by excerpts from documentaries and feature films, essays, poems, short stories and novels as well as art and music characteristic of the periods under discussion.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at providing students with an overview of the key events in the 20th-century British and Irish histories and the effect they had on the image and influence of the countries in the world as well as of the competing historical interpretations of them.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who complete the course successfully will 1) know the key events of  the 20th-century British and Irish histories, 2) understand their effect on the image and influence of the two countries in the world today, 3) explain the key trends in Great Britain and Ireland (the emancipation of women, the Irish question, the demise of the British Empire, the development of democracy and of popular culture, immigration) in the 20th century, 4) locate and use in their research primary and secondary sources (archive records and other documentary evidence, newspaper articles, photos, films, newsreels, audio records, etc) from the period, 5) evaluate and synthesise competing interpretations of the 20th-century British and Irish histories.
